    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="86"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.51/800½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Latin American
                        Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-11">October 11,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Kent telephoned from New York regarding the Brazilian proposal for servicing
                    Brazil’s foreign debts and read to me an extract from a letter he had written
                    last week to the Brazilian Minister of Finance. In this letter Mr. Kent
                    expressed the view that the American loans (federal) in group three really
                    should be in group one, since these loans had been included in the 1931 funding
                    plan. As group one provides for full service covering both interest and sinking
                    fund, and group three provides for only partial service, he felt there was an
                    element of discrimination against the American issues.</p>
                <p>I asked Mr. Kent if he would send me a copy of that portion of his letter dealing
                    with this matter and he said he would.<note n="59" xml:id="d86fn59">Letter not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin C. Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
